PRIMARY GAMMA TRANS.FROM
DY-165. ALL TRANSITIONS WHOSE ENERGIES DIFFER FROM THE
NEUTRON BINDING ENERGY IN DY-165 (B = 5715.76 KEV) BY
LESS THAN ABOUT 2 MEV AND WHOSE INTENSITIES ARE LARGER
THAN 20 PHOTONS/100000 NEUTRON CAPTURES IN DY-164 WERE
ASSUMED TO BE PRIMARY.
THE HIGH FLUX REACTOR AT ILL, GRENOBLE
.THERMAL NEUTRON SPECTRUM WITH A FLUX OF 5.5E+14
NEUTRONS/CM2/SEC.
.20 MG OF DY2O3 POWDER, ENRICHED TO 95.7 PERCENT IN
IN-BEAM GAMMA SPECTROSCOPY.
THE HIGH-ENERGY GAMMA-RAYS (E GT. 3.5 MEV) WERE
DETECTED WITH A PAIR SPECTROMETER, CONSISTING OF A
HYPER-PURE GERMANIUM DETECTOR, PLACED BETWEEN
TWO NAI(TL) CRYSTALS. THE RESOLUTION OF THE
PAIR SPECTROMETER WAS 2.3 KEV AT 2.3 MEV AND 5.5 KEV
AT 7.6 MEV. THE SPECTROMETER WAS ENERGY CALIBRATED
USING GAMMAS FROM THE AL-27(N,G) REACTION. THE INTEN-
SITY CALIBRATION WAS BASED ON THE ABSOLUTE INTENSITIES
OF A FEW STRON TRANSITIONS IN DY-165.

x4freetext: BR2 REACTOR AT MOL FOR DISTINGUISHING
GAMMA-RAYS COMING FROM DOUBLE CAPTURE IN DY-164
.THERMAL NEUTRON SPECTRUM. THE NEUTRON FLUX AT ILL WAS
5.5E+14 NEUTRONS/CM2/SEC, AND AT MOL ABOUT 1.E+13 NEU-
TRONS/CM2/SEC.
.20 MG OF DY2O3 POWDER, ENRICHED TO 95.7 PERCENT IN
IN-BEAM GAMMA SPECTROSCOPY. THE LINES COMING
FROM DOUBLE CAPTURE IN DY-164 WERE DISTINGUISHED BY
THE DIFFERENT TIME DEPENDENCES AND BY MAKING USE OF
THE DIFFERENT FLUXES AT THE ILL AND MOL INSTRUMENTS.
.BENT-CRYSTAL DIFFRACTION SPECTROMETERS GAMS1 AND
GAMS2/3 AT ILL, AND THE SIMILAR INSTRUMENT AT MOL.
.SECONDARY GAMMA-RAYS BETWEEN 46 AND 750 KEV WERE DE-
TECTED IN STEPS OF 0.9 ARCSECONDS WITH GAMS1. AT THE
SAME TIME GAMS2/3 WAS USED TO SCAN THE ENRGY REGION
FROM 104 TO 2500 KEV IN STEPS OF 0.33 ARCSECONDS. THE
COUNTING TIME WAS 60 SEC./POINT. THE SPECTRUM BETWEEN
112 AND 2000 KEV WAS ALSO REMEASURED IN A SECOND
GAMS2/3 RUN. THE ANGULAR RESOLUTION FOR GAMS1 VARIED
BETWEEN 4 AND 5 ARCSECONDS, CORRESPONDING TO AN ENERGY
RESOLUTION OF 120 EV AT 200 KEV. THE ANGULAR RESOLU-
TION FOR GAMS2/3 VARIED BETWEEN 0.9 AND 1.6 ARCSE-
CONDS, WHICH CORRESPONDS TO AN ENERGY RESOLUTION OF
360 EV AT 800 KEV.
.THE RELATIVE ENERGY CALIBRATION WAS PERFORMED BY RE-
QUIRING THAT A GAMMA-TRANSITION HAS THE SAME ENERGY IN
ALL DIFFRACTION ORDERS. THE INTENSITY CALIBRATION WAS
PERFORMED ON THE BASIS OF THE ABSOLUTE INTENSITIES OF
.THE BENT-CRYSTAL DIFFRACTION SPECTROMETER AT MOL MAKES
USE OF A HIGHLY PERFECT SILICIUM CRYSTAL.
.THE ENERGY INTERVAL BETWEEN 230 AND 1600 KEV WAS MEA-
SURED IN STEPS OF 0.5 ARCSECONDS WITH A COUNTING TIME
OF 1000 SEC./STEP. THE LINE WIDTH WAS 1.7 ARCSECONDS,
CORRESPONDING TO AN ENERGY RESOLUTION OF 2.6E-6E**2/N.
NO DETAILS GIVEN.
